<DOC><DOCNO> AP880611-0011 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-11-88 0345EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Japan-Bribery     06-11 0179</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Japan-Bribery,0185</SECOND><HEAD>Former Prime Minister's Office Official Arrested For Taking Bribes</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Japanese authorities have arrested a former publicrelations officer with the Prime Minister's Office for allegedlyaccepting bribes from an advertising company, authorities saidtoday.   Officials from the Tokyo prosecutor's office on Friday arrestedShigeru Suzuki, 59, a former councilor in charge of governmentpublic relations, for accepting bribes in return for extendingfavors, said the official, who spoke on condition of anonymity.   Also arrested were two men who allegedly offered the bribes toSuzuki: Saburo Toyama, 67, chairman of an Osaka-based advertisingcompany, and Tsutomu Nishida, 56, head of its Tokyo branch.   The Asahi Shimbun, a nationally circulated daily, reported todaythat investigators found the two had entertained Suzuki withdinners in Tokyo and golf outings costing a total of $7,200.   The entertainment led to increased orders for televisionadvertisements, the report said.   The prosecutor's office refused to confirm or deny the report.   Another former Prime Minister's Office official was arrested inMay for allegedly accepting about $18,400 in bribes fromadvertising agents.</TEXT></DOC>